Intellisense raises weired error CS0411 when
* create 2 project: LibraryA and LibraryB that are LangVersion:13.0
* and LibraryB project references LibraryA project
* use different targetframework between LibraryA and LibraryB (e.g. LibraryB: net8.0, LibraryA: netstandard2.1)
* define overloaded methods in LibraryA with polyfill `OverloadResolutionPriorityAttribute`
* use overloaded method in LibraryB that references LibraryA
* when selected overload method has less priority of OverloadResolutionPriorityAttribute value
* Intellisense shows an error CS0411 but project can be built successfully

## reproduction code

### LibraryA (netstandard2.1)
```csharp
namespace System.Runtime.CompilerServices
{
    [AttributeUsage(AttributeTargets.Constructor | AttributeTargets.Method | AttributeTargets.Property, AllowMultiple = false, Inherited = false)]
    internal sealed class OverloadResolutionPriorityAttribute(int priority) : Attribute
    {
        public int Priority =&gt; priority;
    }
}

namespace LibraryA
{
    public class Class1
    {
        public void Method&lt;T&gt;(T item) { }
        public void Method&lt;T&gt;(IEnumerable&lt;T&gt; items) { }

        public void MethodWithOverloadResolutionPriority&lt;T&gt;(T item) { }
        [System.Runtime.CompilerServices.OverloadResolutionPriority(1)]
        public void MethodWithOverloadResolutionPriority&lt;T&gt;(IEnumerable&lt;T&gt; items) { }
    }
}
```

### LibraryB (net8.0)
```csharp
using LibraryA;

public class LibraryB
{
    public void Method()
    {
        var class1 = new Class1();

        var integer = 1;
        var enumerable = Enumerable.Empty&lt;int&gt;();
        var array = Array.Empty&lt;int&gt;();

        class1.Method(integer); // OK: Method&lt;int&gt;(int item)
        class1.Method(enumerable); // OK: Method&lt;int&gt;(IEnumerable&lt;int&gt; items)
        class1.Method(array); // OK: Method&lt;int[]&gt;(int[] item) // &lt;- need OverloadResolutionPriority

        class1.MethodWithOverloadResolutionPriority(integer); // NG: CS0411 Intellisense Error! but can compile
        class1.MethodWithOverloadResolutionPriority(enumerable); // OK: MethodWithOverloadResolutionPriority&lt;int&gt;(IEnumerable&lt;int&gt; items)
        class1.MethodWithOverloadResolutionPriority(array); // OK: MethodWithOverloadResolutionPriority&lt;int&gt;(IEnumerable&lt;int&gt; items)
    }
}
```

other investigations:
* if LibraryA and LibraryB are same targetframework (e.g. both netstandard2.1, both net8.0), Intellisense works fine
* built assembly with Intellisense error works as intended

